WEBVTT

00:03.291 --> 00:05.083
♪ OHHH OHHH OHHH ♪

00:06.542 --> 00:08.542
( upbeat pop music playing )

00:11.542 --> 00:14.000
I hate surprises.
I always have.

00:14.041 --> 00:16.291
And surprise parties?
Oh, they're the worst.

00:16.333 --> 00:18.917
They are designed to make
you feel completely unsettled.

00:18.959 --> 00:21.125
Your friends won't talk to you
about birthday plans,

00:21.166 --> 00:23.333
so you think they've forgotten
or just don't care.

00:23.375 --> 00:25.041
And then when you try
to set something up,

00:25.083 --> 00:26.542
suddenly everybody's busy.

00:26.583 --> 00:28.792
And you catch your friends
whispering to each other,

00:28.834 --> 00:31.583
and then they suddenly stop
when you come by. And for what?

00:31.625 --> 00:34.417
So these same friends can gather
in a dark room somewhere

00:34.458 --> 00:35.625
with the sole intention

00:35.667 --> 00:38.041
of scaring
the now totally depressed

00:38.083 --> 00:41.959
and completely paranoid birthday
girl by screaming "surprise"?

00:42.000 --> 00:42.959
I mean, who needs that?

00:43.000 --> 00:44.750
But isn't there a payoff?

00:44.792 --> 00:46.125
You're surrounded by people

00:46.166 --> 00:49.542
who have gathered in your honor
to express their love.

00:49.583 --> 00:52.750
( laughs )

00:52.792 --> 00:57.000
Uh, no. No, that is not how love
is supposed to feel.

00:59.208 --> 01:00.500
Morning, beauty.

01:08.083 --> 01:10.000
( Violet inhales deeply )

01:10.041 --> 01:12.792
What?
You don't have to do that.

01:12.834 --> 01:15.625
Kiss you?
No. Bring me coffee.

01:15.667 --> 01:17.041
You absolutely
have to kiss me.

01:17.083 --> 01:19.834
I also brought you
the real estate section.

01:19.875 --> 01:23.625
I figured you might wanna
start thinking about moving.

01:23.667 --> 01:25.834
There was a guy killed
right there.

01:25.875 --> 01:27.875
Not to mention
the woman who attacked you.

01:27.917 --> 01:29.041
How do you know about that?

01:29.083 --> 01:31.208
I read your book.

01:31.250 --> 01:32.667
I do know how to read.

01:32.709 --> 01:36.208
It's looking, um, good.

01:36.250 --> 01:38.291
Maybe make it better?

01:47.500 --> 01:48.834
Um...

01:48.875 --> 01:50.458
I thought you'd be
at work already.

01:50.500 --> 01:52.041
You're early.

01:52.083 --> 01:54.208
Hey. Did you have fun
with Dad last night?

01:54.250 --> 01:55.208
LUCAS:
Mm-hm.

01:55.250 --> 01:56.625
Yeah.
So do you still want me

01:56.667 --> 02:00.458
to wait for the nanny
or are you gonna stick around?

02:00.500 --> 02:03.583
Oh, right.
Uh, no, you can go. Thanks.

02:04.917 --> 02:07.250
Love you.
I'll see you later.

02:07.291 --> 02:08.709
Have a good day, Dr. Wilder.

02:12.333 --> 02:13.667
The nightmares started

02:13.709 --> 02:16.250
right when he got back
from Afghanistan.

02:16.291 --> 02:19.250
And then
he just stopped sleeping

02:19.291 --> 02:21.667
because I guess
who wants to sleep

02:21.709 --> 02:23.291
when you're always
waking up screaming.

02:23.333 --> 02:25.917
It's common for soldiers
to have problems

02:25.959 --> 02:30.083
turning off the siege mentality
they've been living 24/7.

02:30.125 --> 02:31.667
KELLY:
I was so excited

02:31.709 --> 02:33.291
for his service to be done,

02:33.333 --> 02:38.291
that I could stop worrying about
whether he'd come home alive.

02:38.333 --> 02:39.750
But I did.

02:41.083 --> 02:42.166
So now we can move on.

02:42.208 --> 02:46.917
But we're not,
and you're so distant.

02:46.959 --> 02:49.917
I've tried talking

02:49.959 --> 02:53.291
and I've tried giving him space.

02:53.333 --> 02:55.125
I've even tried
new lingerie.

02:55.166 --> 02:56.375
( sighs )

02:56.417 --> 03:00.500
But sex,
he's just not interested.

03:00.542 --> 03:02.125
Kelly.

03:02.166 --> 03:04.500
I touch you
and you just freeze.

03:04.542 --> 03:08.125
Look, I know what it means
to be a military wife.

03:08.166 --> 03:11.041
My father was a soldier,
got wounded in Vietnam.

03:11.083 --> 03:13.625
And I know that the guys
need help when they come home.

03:13.667 --> 03:16.208
So I read
about couples therapy.

03:16.250 --> 03:19.166
I thought, "What the hell?
It couldn't hurt."

03:19.208 --> 03:22.125
But it doesn't help
if we're not honest.

03:22.166 --> 03:24.041
Sometimes it's useful
to me to see

03:24.083 --> 03:27.333
the husband and wife separately,
as well as together.

03:27.375 --> 03:29.542
It can make it easier
to talk that way.

03:29.583 --> 03:30.959
He won't talk
about anything.

03:31.000 --> 03:35.166
What do you want me to say?
What happened there...

03:35.208 --> 03:36.583
I don't wanna bring it here.

03:36.625 --> 03:39.041
But it is here.

03:39.083 --> 03:40.834
Right between us.

03:42.917 --> 03:47.166
I will do anything to get
us back on track. Please,

03:47.208 --> 03:49.709
just tell me what I can do.

03:59.083 --> 04:01.834
JAKE:
Couldn't call it a better name
than Scientific Assembly

04:01.875 --> 04:03.834
for the College of Obstetrics
and Gynecology?

04:03.875 --> 04:07.875
It's hard to believe the acronym
SACOG isn't sweeping the nation.

04:07.917 --> 04:09.792
You can put your stuff
in my car.

04:09.834 --> 04:12.166
Uh, you know what,
let's take my car.

04:12.208 --> 04:13.417
Why?

04:13.458 --> 04:15.458
Because, you know,
a man drives.

04:15.500 --> 04:17.041
Seriously?

04:17.083 --> 04:20.250
What, I mean, you don't trust
a woman behind the wheel?

04:20.291 --> 04:22.041
No, I'm sure
you're a fantastic driver,

04:22.083 --> 04:23.041
but, you know, it's...

04:23.083 --> 04:24.500
What, I might get the vapors

04:24.542 --> 04:26.041
between here
and Palm Springs?

04:26.083 --> 04:27.250
It's not
a sexist thing, okay?

04:27.291 --> 04:28.458
I'm just old-fashioned.

04:28.500 --> 04:30.250
I was taught
that a man pulls out a chair,

04:30.291 --> 04:32.917
a man opens doors,
and a man drives a woman.

04:32.959 --> 04:35.875
Fine. I don't wanna go
to this thing anyway,

04:35.917 --> 04:38.041
so if it makes you feel better,
you can drive,

04:38.083 --> 04:39.875
but I pick the music.

04:39.917 --> 04:42.000
JAKE:
I got it.

04:46.542 --> 04:48.125
There he is.

04:48.166 --> 04:50.041
Hey. Welcome back, corporal.

04:50.083 --> 04:52.750
Hey, thanks for telling us
about Dr. Wallace.

04:52.792 --> 04:55.083
No problem. No problem.
When are we gonna catch up?

04:55.125 --> 04:57.667
Grab a beer,
watch some hoops?

04:57.709 --> 04:59.667
Yeah, I'm pretty busy right now,
you know.

04:59.709 --> 05:00.750
Okay.

05:00.792 --> 05:02.250
All he does
is mope around the house.

05:02.291 --> 05:04.333
You should just come by.
All right, I'll do that.

05:04.375 --> 05:05.709
Okay.
Good to see you.

05:05.750 --> 05:06.875
You too.
All right.

05:06.917 --> 05:08.458
Take care.

05:08.500 --> 05:10.291
RICK:
Bye.

05:10.333 --> 05:12.667
So you think
you can help them?

05:12.709 --> 05:15.041
I don't know yet. Your friend
isn't much of a talker.

05:15.083 --> 05:17.333
He's always been
a private type of guy.

05:17.375 --> 05:18.667
We worked together at church

05:18.709 --> 05:20.709
on this program
he started for at-risk kids,

05:20.750 --> 05:22.917
but I don't know
if he's a therapy type.

05:22.959 --> 05:24.291
There's no type, Sam.

05:24.333 --> 05:27.083
And Kelly's right,
he does need help.

05:27.125 --> 05:28.917
Well, he did just
get back from the war,

05:28.959 --> 05:31.125
so maybe he just needs some
time. Thanks.

05:33.542 --> 05:35.583
Okay, I can do
two night shifts a week

05:35.625 --> 05:37.291
and a third
every other week.

05:37.333 --> 05:39.917
That way, I'm clear
for my time with Lucas.

05:39.959 --> 05:41.500
So you and Violet
are still...?

05:41.542 --> 05:44.041
Yeah, we needed
this separation.

05:44.083 --> 05:46.125
Is that all it is
or you talking divorce?

05:46.166 --> 05:47.500
PARAMEDIC:
MVA on the 405.

05:47.542 --> 05:49.291
Victim is
a 34-year-old female,

05:49.333 --> 05:50.750
in and out of consciousness,

05:50.792 --> 05:52.959
wasn't able to follow commands
to move her extremities.

05:53.000 --> 05:55.083
PETE: Charlotte, is that...?
Erica.

05:55.125 --> 05:56.792
I need a C-spine,
chest and pelvis,

05:56.834 --> 05:58.333
trauma panel and CT.
NURSE: Got it.

05:58.375 --> 06:00.625
Where's Mason? Was he with her?
He's her son.

06:00.667 --> 06:02.208
PARAMEDIC:
One, two, three.

06:02.250 --> 06:04.041
Mason.

06:04.083 --> 06:05.625
( tense theme playing )

06:05.667 --> 06:08.125
CHARLOTTE: Are you okay?
He's got facial lacerations

06:08.166 --> 06:10.041
from broken glass
and an abrasion on his chest

06:10.083 --> 06:11.834
from the seat belt,
but he's good.

06:11.875 --> 06:13.458
Where's my mom?
I need my mom.

06:21.166 --> 06:23.625
( knocking )

06:23.667 --> 06:26.041
Rick, it's Sam.

06:26.083 --> 06:27.667
I know you're in there.

06:27.709 --> 06:29.917
I see your truck
in the driveway.

06:31.500 --> 06:32.625
Ricky!

06:33.834 --> 06:36.417
Rick. Whoa.

06:36.458 --> 06:38.583
A little early
to be tying one on.

06:38.625 --> 06:40.458
Don't--

06:40.500 --> 06:43.041
( tender theme playing )

06:43.083 --> 06:44.041
Rick.

06:44.083 --> 06:46.500
Damn it.

06:51.083 --> 06:54.041
Yeah. Hello.
This is Dr. Sam Bennett.

06:54.083 --> 06:57.417
I need an ambulance immediately
at 5110 Patrick Henry.

06:57.458 --> 07:00.542
We got a probable overdose,
a 25-year-old male.

07:10.083 --> 07:11.083
Why am I still alive?

07:11.125 --> 07:12.709
Well, I found you in time.

07:12.750 --> 07:13.875
We had to give you charcoal

07:13.917 --> 07:15.667
to absorb all the pills
that you took.

07:15.709 --> 07:18.083
You shouldn't have done that.
SHELDON: You can't go.

07:18.125 --> 07:20.625
You're on psych hold till I can
be sure you won't hurt yourself.

07:20.667 --> 07:21.875
Go to hell.

07:21.917 --> 07:23.458
All right, take it easy.
You can stop me?

07:23.500 --> 07:24.625
All I wanna do is talk.

07:24.667 --> 07:26.458
No, don't touch me!
Hey. All right.

07:26.500 --> 07:27.917
Get off me!
A little help here.

07:27.959 --> 07:28.917
RICK:
Don't!

07:28.959 --> 07:30.834
Haloperidol,
five milligrams, IM now.

07:30.875 --> 07:32.041
Get his arms.

07:32.083 --> 07:34.458
Easy. Okay.

07:34.500 --> 07:36.917
( Rick grunts then sighs )

07:38.792 --> 07:40.041
SAM:
All right.

07:40.083 --> 07:42.875
C-spine is clear.
No fracture or dislocation.

07:42.917 --> 07:44.041
What's her neuro status?

07:44.083 --> 07:45.500
I'm doing a repeat exam now.

07:45.542 --> 07:47.041
What happened? Where am I?

07:47.083 --> 07:48.542
You were in a car accident.

07:48.583 --> 07:49.875
Where's Mason?

07:49.917 --> 07:51.291
MASON:
Mom?

07:52.333 --> 07:54.291
I'm here.

07:54.333 --> 07:56.041
What happened?

07:56.083 --> 07:59.041
She can see you
in a little while, okay?

07:59.083 --> 08:00.625
She has a gliosarcoma.

08:00.667 --> 08:02.125
Could be causing
the disorientation.

08:02.166 --> 08:04.041
Where am I? What happened?

08:04.083 --> 08:07.083
You lost consciousness, Erica.
It's normal to feel confused.

08:07.125 --> 08:10.083
Give her five of lorazepam
before you take her to CT.

08:10.125 --> 08:13.375
Hey. Are you okay?
Does it hurt anywhere?

08:13.417 --> 08:15.709
No. She made me wear a seat belt
and sit in the back.

08:15.750 --> 08:18.709
Okay. What happened?
Do you remember what happened?

08:18.750 --> 08:20.000
We were driving to school

08:20.041 --> 08:21.709
and we were talking
about my book report

08:21.750 --> 08:24.917
and she just fell asleep,
and let go of the wheel.

08:24.959 --> 08:26.792
CHARLOTTE:
Mason, we're gonna take your mom

08:26.834 --> 08:29.125
for some tests.
You stay here with your dad.

08:30.166 --> 08:31.709
Is my mom gonna be okay?

08:31.750 --> 08:33.542
Yeah, yeah.

08:35.083 --> 08:36.125
( sighs )

08:50.166 --> 08:52.041
Kelly's on her way.

08:52.083 --> 08:54.417
I don't wanna see her.

08:54.458 --> 08:56.166
That's fine.
You don't have to.

08:56.208 --> 08:58.041
But you and I,

08:58.083 --> 09:00.834
we're gonna need to talk about
what just happened,

09:00.875 --> 09:02.250
what you tried to do.

09:04.083 --> 09:06.458
I know this is a hard time.

09:08.000 --> 09:10.041
And leaving the familiar
structure of the military

09:10.083 --> 09:12.667
can be disorienting. Especially
when you've been at war.

09:14.083 --> 09:15.875
It wasn't what I expected.

09:15.917 --> 09:18.041
Of course.

09:18.083 --> 09:20.083
No matter what you imagine,

09:21.250 --> 09:24.083
base impulse
just to survive is threatened.

09:24.125 --> 09:27.917
I just wanted it
all to stop.

09:29.083 --> 09:34.041
I kept thinking about
being sent home in a body bag,

09:34.083 --> 09:37.500
how that would
at least be a release.

09:39.250 --> 09:42.041
Wanting to die,
that's not unusual

09:42.083 --> 09:44.000
given the stress
you've been under,

09:44.041 --> 09:45.875
but it becomes
a very serious problem

09:45.917 --> 09:48.834
when you actually try
to take your own life.

09:55.083 --> 09:56.709
Talk about
what you were thinking

09:56.750 --> 09:59.875
when you made the decision
to take those pills.

10:01.750 --> 10:03.709
I signed up
for the fighting.

10:05.125 --> 10:07.250
That's what
I was trained for.

10:07.291 --> 10:08.542
I was prepared for that.

10:09.667 --> 10:13.291
What weren't you
prepared for?

10:13.333 --> 10:15.917
You know, your reaction
when I put my hands on you--

10:15.959 --> 10:17.041
I fought back.

10:17.083 --> 10:20.041
I wasn't trying to hurt you.

10:20.083 --> 10:21.542
You know that, right?

10:24.083 --> 10:25.583
I don't like
being caught off-guard.

10:26.709 --> 10:28.000
When were you
caught off-guard?

10:29.709 --> 10:31.792
Who caught you off-guard?

10:34.709 --> 10:37.041
Was it someone you trusted?

10:37.083 --> 10:39.041
I know
there's hazing in the military.

10:39.083 --> 10:41.875
Were you a victim?
Or a perpetrator?

10:41.917 --> 10:44.041
I would never hurt someone
like that.

10:44.083 --> 10:45.125
Did someone hurt you?

10:46.792 --> 10:48.917
Who was it?

10:51.083 --> 10:53.000
( tense theme playing )

10:54.125 --> 10:56.959
It was my sergeant.

10:58.542 --> 11:00.834
What did he do?

11:00.875 --> 11:02.500
What did he do to you?

11:02.542 --> 11:05.542
Your sergeant,
did he assault you?

11:09.542 --> 11:12.750
He raped me, okay?

11:12.792 --> 11:14.000
My sergeant raped me.

11:23.083 --> 11:26.542
I think we can do without these,
right?

11:33.000 --> 11:34.208
You can't tell anyone.

11:34.250 --> 11:36.000
I won't.

11:37.083 --> 11:39.000
Because this...

11:39.041 --> 11:41.625
My life is over.

11:41.667 --> 11:45.041
No, it's not. I know
you may feel that way, but it...

11:45.083 --> 11:47.625
Look, I don't think you agreed
to couple's counseling

11:47.667 --> 11:49.625
just for Kelly's benefit.

11:49.667 --> 11:52.041
Most soldiers who are serious
about killing themselves,

11:52.083 --> 11:54.125
they use their weapons.

11:54.166 --> 11:58.000
So that makes me think
that you don't wanna die.

11:59.458 --> 12:01.583
You wanna talk,

12:01.625 --> 12:04.000
and I wanna listen.

12:08.083 --> 12:10.625
You said it was your sergeant,
right?

12:11.917 --> 12:14.000
Sergeant Hamill.

12:17.417 --> 12:20.625
He backhanded me
across the jaw.

12:20.667 --> 12:25.000
He knocked my feet out and
then he kicked me to the ground.

12:29.083 --> 12:33.000
He braced one arm
against my neck.

12:35.083 --> 12:39.959
I swear, I thought
he was gonna snap my spine.

12:41.125 --> 12:43.250
I couldn't speak,

12:43.291 --> 12:45.959
I couldn't move.

12:47.083 --> 12:49.667
It didn't seem real.

12:51.458 --> 12:54.208
Until he...

12:54.250 --> 12:59.500
He tore open my uniform
and he jammed himself...

13:01.875 --> 13:04.333
I wish I'd died right then.

13:07.709 --> 13:09.083
You were incredibly brave.

13:12.083 --> 13:14.500
What the hell
are you talking about?

13:16.083 --> 13:18.667
I was weak.
I let him rape me.

13:18.709 --> 13:20.083
No.

13:20.125 --> 13:22.709
He was a psychopath.

13:22.750 --> 13:25.458
And you let yourself live.

13:25.500 --> 13:27.500
( soft theme playing )

13:33.291 --> 13:34.667
Hey, about this morning.

13:34.709 --> 13:37.041
I didn't mean
to make you feel uncomfortable.

13:37.083 --> 13:40.667
Well, it isn't about me.
Lucas almost saw you.

13:40.709 --> 13:43.166
But he didn't.
This time.

13:43.208 --> 13:45.500
Maybe you shouldn't have
your friend over

13:45.542 --> 13:47.083
when you know Lucas
is gonna be there.

13:47.125 --> 13:50.041
First of all, I didn't know that
Scott was gonna be dropping by.

13:50.083 --> 13:52.291
And second of all, seriously?
I know this bothers you--

13:52.333 --> 13:54.333
Just keep him away
from Lucas.

13:54.375 --> 13:56.542
Hey, Pete.

13:57.792 --> 13:59.291
Hey. I just heard about

13:59.333 --> 14:01.041
Mason and Erica.
How are they doing?

14:01.083 --> 14:03.291
Erica has a concussion,
but no serious injuries.

14:03.333 --> 14:05.792
Mason is pretty freaked out

14:05.834 --> 14:08.041
after watching his mother
fall asleep at the wheel.

14:08.083 --> 14:09.959
I'm so sorry. That's awful.
I know.

14:10.000 --> 14:12.417
I'm just trying
to hang on here and...

14:13.750 --> 14:15.208
Are you having
more Pete drama?

14:15.250 --> 14:17.750
Oh, man. It's just silly.
It's nothing, really.

14:17.792 --> 14:20.000
I could use a little silly.
What happened?

14:20.041 --> 14:22.625
Um... This morning,

14:22.667 --> 14:24.625
Pete walked in on me
kissing a guy.

14:24.667 --> 14:26.375
Who's the guy?
Uh--

14:26.417 --> 14:28.583
You know, it's a paramedic.
It's a guy named Scott.

14:28.625 --> 14:30.041
From St. Ambrose?
The young guy?

14:30.083 --> 14:31.041
He's old enough.

14:31.083 --> 14:32.041
That's not what I meant.

14:32.083 --> 14:33.583
He's very handsome.

14:33.625 --> 14:36.041
Does he need a booster seat
in the ambulance

14:36.083 --> 14:38.041
to, like, see over
the steering wheel?

14:38.083 --> 14:39.625
He just-- Sorry.

14:39.667 --> 14:43.000
Pete had Lucas with him when
he walked in on us this morning.

14:43.041 --> 14:44.041
Oh.

14:44.083 --> 14:45.625
I understand Pete
not wanting Lucas

14:45.667 --> 14:48.041
seeing you doing some guy--
I'm not doing him.

14:48.083 --> 14:49.041
I'm-- We're not doing it.

14:49.083 --> 14:52.417
We're just
like fooling around.

14:52.458 --> 14:53.875
It's kind of like
in high school.

14:53.917 --> 14:55.625
When it was
all lips and hands

14:55.667 --> 14:58.041
and swoony, unconsummated--

14:58.083 --> 15:01.625
Okay, okay.
Did Lucas see you?

15:01.667 --> 15:05.041
No.
Then it's Pete's ego talking.

15:05.083 --> 15:07.875
You guys are separated, right?
You get to date other people?

15:07.917 --> 15:09.875
I don't know what
the hard-and-fast rules are.

15:09.917 --> 15:11.041
I mean, what do you think?

15:11.083 --> 15:13.041
Think it's crazy for me
to be seeing somebody

15:13.083 --> 15:14.583
while Pete and I are--

15:14.625 --> 15:16.375
