You're a soldier.

28:55.083 --> 28:59.041
He was too.
There wasn't a gang or...?

28:59.083 --> 29:03.041
It wasn't some type of hazing
or something?

29:03.083 --> 29:06.375
Are you trying to tell me
that you're gay?

29:06.417 --> 29:08.000
No, he attacked me!

29:08.041 --> 29:10.041
KELLY:
Because I've heard

29:10.083 --> 29:12.041
about men who like other men

29:12.083 --> 29:13.208
and they just don't know

29:13.250 --> 29:15.250
how to tell their wives.
That's not what happened.

29:15.291 --> 29:17.250
Then why didn't you
stop him?

29:17.291 --> 29:19.000
( tense theme playing )

29:28.083 --> 29:29.667
She needs time to process.

29:29.709 --> 29:31.625
Time won't matter.

29:31.667 --> 29:34.000
She said exactly
what I've been thinking myself.

29:42.667 --> 29:44.041
Oh, my God.

29:44.083 --> 29:46.041
JAKE:
It's okay.

29:46.083 --> 29:48.208
Oh, my God.
It's okay.

29:48.250 --> 29:49.875
( gasps )

29:49.917 --> 29:53.250
Oh, crap.
I'm late for my presentation.

29:53.291 --> 29:56.458
I had them move you to 4 p.m.
You've got three more hours.

29:56.500 --> 29:59.041
( sighs )

29:59.083 --> 30:01.125
Oh.

30:01.166 --> 30:03.125
Did I ask you for sex
and then cry?

30:03.166 --> 30:05.291
I have no idea
what you're talking about.

30:07.166 --> 30:09.041
Okay. I, uh--

30:09.083 --> 30:10.709
I'm so sorry.

30:10.750 --> 30:15.083
I had a lot to drink last night
and it was a bad idea

30:15.125 --> 30:17.667
and my sad just sort of came out
all over you.

30:17.709 --> 30:20.041
I am so, so, so sorry.

30:20.083 --> 30:22.917
It's okay.
No, it's really not.

30:22.959 --> 30:26.083
I feel like I'm always
a mess around you

30:26.125 --> 30:27.291
and it's not good, you know?

30:27.333 --> 30:29.542
We're colleagues.
I'm not this person.

30:29.583 --> 30:30.917
Seriously, I'm not.

30:30.959 --> 30:32.542
We're not gonna talk
about this anymore.

30:32.583 --> 30:35.041
I called room service,
got you a bacon cheeseburger.

30:35.083 --> 30:37.041
It got here five minutes ago.
It's still hot.

30:37.083 --> 30:38.041
Okay, but I--

30:38.083 --> 30:39.291
We're not gonna
talk about this.

30:39.333 --> 30:41.959
Go. Sit. Eat.

30:52.333 --> 30:54.125
I'm supposed to
just do everything you say?

30:54.166 --> 30:56.041
I'm driving.

30:56.083 --> 30:58.041
Eat.

31:01.542 --> 31:04.208
We're not just colleagues.

31:04.250 --> 31:06.792
( slow reggae-pop music
playing )

31:13.417 --> 31:15.041
Hey, Dr. Wilder.

31:15.083 --> 31:16.834
Save it.

31:16.875 --> 31:18.625
Don't, um--

31:18.667 --> 31:20.375
Don't be like that.

31:21.875 --> 31:24.041
You were kissing my wife.
Former wife.

31:24.083 --> 31:28.208
You guys are separated
and I'm not trying to be a jerk.

31:28.250 --> 31:30.000
You know, just shut up.

31:30.041 --> 31:33.458
And know that
if you hurt her

31:33.500 --> 31:36.041
or if you fool around with her
in front of my son--

31:36.083 --> 31:39.208
Then, what?

31:44.041 --> 31:46.208
Yeah. That's what I thought.

31:46.250 --> 31:47.208
CHARLOTTE:
Hey there.

31:47.250 --> 31:48.458
ERICA:
Hey.

31:49.709 --> 31:51.667
( Erica sighs )

31:51.709 --> 31:55.583
So does he stay mad
a long time?

31:55.625 --> 31:57.458
Your husband?

31:57.500 --> 32:00.542
Not as long as I usually do.

32:00.583 --> 32:02.875
But he is fierce about Mason.

32:02.917 --> 32:04.041
( knock on door )

32:04.083 --> 32:06.041
Hey. Somebody would
like to see you.

32:06.083 --> 32:07.333
Oh, baby.

32:12.083 --> 32:14.667
Thank you for bringing him.

32:14.709 --> 32:17.291
I'm so sorry I scared you.

32:17.333 --> 32:20.083
When can we go home?

32:20.125 --> 32:21.208
Soon.

32:21.250 --> 32:23.625
Mommy's feeling much better.

32:23.667 --> 32:27.041
We just have to watch your mom
a day or two longer.

32:27.083 --> 32:31.041
And you can stay
with me and Charlotte, okay?

32:31.083 --> 32:34.041
And you can play
as many video games as you want.

32:34.083 --> 32:35.333
MASON:
I wish you could play too.

32:35.375 --> 32:36.500
( Erica laughs )

32:38.500 --> 32:40.041
( Erica gasping )

32:40.083 --> 32:41.917
( monitor beeping rapidly )

32:41.959 --> 32:43.875
MASON:
Mom. Mom.

32:43.917 --> 32:45.333
Cooper, get him out of here.

32:45.375 --> 32:46.875
COOPER:
Mason, come on. It's okay.

32:46.917 --> 32:48.458
Come on. Come on. Come on.

32:48.500 --> 32:50.750
( grunting )

32:56.709 --> 32:59.041
First he sees his mother
fall asleep

32:59.083 --> 33:01.208
while she's driving him and
then he tries to give her a hug

33:01.250 --> 33:02.709
and she has a seizure.

33:02.750 --> 33:04.041
Coop, I get
that you're mad--

33:04.083 --> 33:06.709
Oh, please, spare me
the lecture, okay?

33:06.750 --> 33:08.041
Violet gave it to me.

33:08.083 --> 33:10.125
I know what stage of grief
I'm in and it doesn't help.

33:10.166 --> 33:12.000
I'm not trying to lecture you.
Good.

33:12.041 --> 33:14.500
Because my son is being hurt

33:14.542 --> 33:17.083
and there's nothing
I can do about it.

33:17.125 --> 33:20.041
I'm not sure that's true.

33:20.083 --> 33:22.291
Look, you can be angry

33:22.333 --> 33:25.709
and sad and frustrated
and a hundred other things.

33:25.750 --> 33:27.041
I don't blame you.

33:27.083 --> 33:29.750
Because there's no easy way
to deal with this.

33:29.792 --> 33:32.291
There is a hard way
to deal with it.

33:32.333 --> 33:34.041
Erica can try to fight.

33:34.083 --> 33:35.792
She may not be successful,

33:35.834 --> 33:40.041
but she could do it
with our help.

33:40.083 --> 33:42.208
I tried.
You demanded.

33:42.250 --> 33:43.750
But you have to remember,

33:43.792 --> 33:47.125
Erica is angry and sad
and frustrated too.

33:47.166 --> 33:49.750
And maybe what she needs right
now isn't someone telling her

33:49.792 --> 33:51.166
that she has to fight
this fight.

33:52.166 --> 33:53.333
Maybe what she needs is

33:53.375 --> 33:54.834
someone helping
her understand

33:54.875 --> 33:57.000
why she should fight it.

33:58.417 --> 33:59.792
KELLY:
He just--

34:01.250 --> 34:02.750
He let it happen.

34:02.792 --> 34:04.625
He didn't let it happen.

34:04.667 --> 34:08.000
Your husband is a survivor
of a sexual assault.

34:10.250 --> 34:14.625
The first time that I saw Rick,
he was on leave,

34:14.667 --> 34:17.583
visiting some high school
buddies and--

34:17.625 --> 34:23.041
I went to this dive bar
with a couple girlfriends

34:23.083 --> 34:25.625
and it had a great jukebox.

34:25.667 --> 34:30.000
And Rick was feeding
every quarter he had into it.

34:31.083 --> 34:35.000
And when
he introduced himself,

34:35.041 --> 34:40.000
he said, "I can't dance,
but for you, I would try."

34:41.417 --> 34:44.667
And when I took his hand,
I thought:

34:44.709 --> 34:47.625
"This man would never
let anything bad happen.

34:49.458 --> 34:52.125
This man would
keep me safe."

34:53.875 --> 34:55.208
That man is gone.

34:55.250 --> 34:57.250
( soft theme playing )

34:59.083 --> 35:03.500
I know that all this
must be a shock to you.

35:03.542 --> 35:07.083
And please forgive me
for even bringing this up,

35:07.125 --> 35:12.250
but if you had been raped
and Rick were to blame you...

35:15.750 --> 35:18.333
When I look at him now,

35:19.750 --> 35:22.291
I don't feel the same.

35:23.917 --> 35:27.000
And I know
how bad that sounds.

35:29.583 --> 35:32.000
I just don't know
what to do.

35:33.542 --> 35:36.041
Didn't you tell me your father
was wounded in Vietnam?

35:36.083 --> 35:40.041
Yeah. He lost his right leg
below the knee.

35:40.083 --> 35:44.500
Well, Rick was wounded
in Afghanistan.

35:45.750 --> 35:49.083
His injury may not be
as visible as your father's,

35:49.125 --> 35:51.333
but it's just as real.

35:53.125 --> 35:56.000
Don't blame him for something
that wasn't his fault.

36:00.041 --> 36:02.041
JAKE:
I was impressed.

36:02.083 --> 36:03.709
I mean, if I had been
that hung-over,

36:03.750 --> 36:07.000
I don't think I could have given
such a focused presentation.

36:07.041 --> 36:10.500
No, I was driven
by shame and humiliation.

36:10.542 --> 36:12.500
Also, the fact
that you promised

36:12.542 --> 36:15.000
we'd stop for another burger
on the way home.

36:15.041 --> 36:17.083
Oh, is that right?
Yeah.

36:17.125 --> 36:20.542
I don't remember that part,
but okay.

36:23.417 --> 36:25.333
Thank you.

36:26.625 --> 36:30.792
For being so amazing last night.
I really...

36:30.834 --> 36:34.542
I appreciate it.
No problem.

36:34.583 --> 36:37.041
And you're wrong, you know.

36:37.083 --> 36:39.542
What?
I've been dumped before.

36:39.583 --> 36:41.041
When I was
on that plane to Fiji

36:41.083 --> 36:42.625
and you weren't in
that seat next to me.

36:42.667 --> 36:45.417
You didn't even wind up going.
Still felt like getting dumped.

36:45.458 --> 36:47.125
It felt like you dumped me.
Jake.

36:47.166 --> 36:49.792
No, I'm just saying,
if someday I get drunk

36:49.834 --> 36:51.417
and show up
on your doorstep,

36:51.458 --> 36:55.166
fat from bacon cheeseburgers
and demanding sex, look out.

36:57.083 --> 37:00.083
( both laugh )

37:03.083 --> 37:04.500
What?

37:07.750 --> 37:08.834
What?

37:08.875 --> 37:11.625
I don't want you
seeing Scott anymore.

37:13.250 --> 37:16.041
That's not really your call.
It is when it affects Lucas.

37:16.083 --> 37:18.000
That's not
what's really bothering you.

37:18.041 --> 37:20.166
Ha. I just love it

37:20.208 --> 37:22.041
when you tell me
what I'm really thinking.

37:22.083 --> 37:23.583
You know what? You left me.

37:23.625 --> 37:27.375
Do you even understand that?
You left me, Pete.

37:27.417 --> 37:30.166
I asked you-- I practically
begged you to stop me

37:30.208 --> 37:32.041
from walking out that door,
but you didn't.

37:32.083 --> 37:35.041
You didn't do a damn thing.
You let me go!

37:35.083 --> 37:38.041
And now you have the audacity,
you have the gall to tell me

37:38.083 --> 37:39.291
that I can't see
someone else?

37:39.333 --> 37:41.417
Fine. Do whatever you want.
I don't care anymore.

37:41.458 --> 37:43.625
You didn't care then.
Why should now be different?

37:43.667 --> 37:44.834
Got to hell, Violet.

37:44.875 --> 37:46.875
( tender theme playing )

37:48.917 --> 37:51.291
I wanna go home.

37:53.083 --> 37:55.417
Let's see how it goes today.

37:55.458 --> 37:58.041
I don't think
Kelly will be there.

37:58.083 --> 38:01.000
She hasn't returned
any of my calls.

38:02.542 --> 38:05.041
I know that's disappointing.

38:05.083 --> 38:09.750
But even if that's the case,
telling her the way you did?

38:09.792 --> 38:10.959
You should be very proud.

38:12.083 --> 38:15.000
Your life still has value,
Rick.

38:23.291 --> 38:24.375
Hey.

38:26.375 --> 38:29.375
( soft theme playing )

38:50.375 --> 38:51.917
You feeling any better?

38:51.959 --> 38:53.375
ERICA:
Yeah.

38:55.375 --> 38:59.291
This whole thing
has been terrifying.

38:59.333 --> 39:01.375
Yeah.
There's no way out.

39:01.417 --> 39:03.792
I can't make it better
and I can't make it easier

39:03.834 --> 39:07.166
and I'm just...stuck

39:07.208 --> 39:09.000
in the worst possible place.

39:10.750 --> 39:12.750
It is a...

39:13.834 --> 39:18.333
terrible situation
for a lot of different reasons.

39:19.417 --> 39:21.125
And look, even though

39:21.166 --> 39:23.333
it doesn't take anywhere
near the amount of courage

39:23.375 --> 39:26.166
for me to ask you this
as it does for you to say yes--

39:26.208 --> 39:28.750
Cooper.
Fight.

39:28.792 --> 39:32.000
Please, Erica. Please fight.

39:33.583 --> 39:38.792
Look, the odds are long
and it's gonna be miserable

39:38.834 --> 39:40.041
and I can't promise you

39:40.083 --> 39:42.041
that you're gonna get
enough extra time

39:42.083 --> 39:44.959
to make the hell
that's chemo or radiation

39:45.000 --> 39:46.750
or whatever they do
to you worth it,

39:46.792 --> 39:48.834
but I can tell you this:

39:48.875 --> 39:51.041
What you're doing now
is not working.

39:52.208 --> 39:54.208
I don't wanna let you go.

39:54.250 --> 39:56.417
I don't think
you're ready to go.

39:56.458 --> 39:58.792
( soft theme playing )

39:58.834 --> 40:00.083
And most importantly...

40:01.500 --> 40:03.041
...maybe we'll get lucky.

40:04.625 --> 40:07.625
Maybe it'll just show Mason
how much you care. Maybe--

40:07.667 --> 40:09.625
I don't know.
I just don't know, Erica.

40:09.667 --> 40:12.667
But please, just fight.

40:17.834 --> 40:19.875
( inaudible dialogue )

40:25.083 --> 40:26.542
Okay.

40:29.250 --> 40:30.750
( sighs )

40:34.917 --> 40:36.417
Hi.
Hi.

40:36.458 --> 40:40.458
Are you okay?
You sounded kind of--

40:40.500 --> 40:42.250
( slow indie-rock music
playing )

40:45.250 --> 40:47.875
Wait a minute.
Is Lucas--? Is--?

40:47.917 --> 40:49.417
He's with his dad.

40:49.458 --> 40:52.667
So Pete's-- He's not here?
No.

40:59.166 --> 41:01.375
( phone ringing )

41:05.917 --> 41:08.000
This is Dr. Sam Bennett.

41:12.500 --> 41:14.041
Wait.
There must be some mistake.

41:14.083 --> 41:16.375
Because I have a--

41:17.709 --> 41:19.709
Okay. Where?

41:22.125 --> 41:24.041
I'll be right there.

41:24.083 --> 41:26.041
I've always been
the kind of person

41:26.083 --> 41:28.041
who reads the last chapter
of the book first.

41:28.083 --> 41:29.291
I like to know
what's coming.

41:29.333 --> 41:31.041
It used to drive Sam crazy.

41:31.083 --> 41:32.500
He'd say to me,
"Getting to the end

41:32.542 --> 41:34.500
is supposed to be
a surprise."

41:34.542 --> 41:36.000
MAN:
It's nice of you to come down.

41:36.041 --> 41:37.542
Most of the people in here?

41:37.583 --> 41:39.291
Nobody shows up
to take them home.

41:39.333 --> 41:40.500
Yeah. Uh...

41:40.542 --> 41:42.041
What was
she arrested for again?

41:42.083 --> 41:45.083
She boosted the cash from
a convenience store register.

41:45.125 --> 41:47.208
Just wait here.
I'll get her.

41:56.625 --> 41:58.417
ADDISON:
I hate surprises.

42:00.083 --> 42:02.000
This is who you came to pick up,
right?

42:02.041 --> 42:04.083
ADDISON:
I like to know.

42:04.125 --> 42:06.208
Uh, yeah.

42:06.250 --> 42:08.125
That's my sister.

42:08.166 --> 42:11.000
I like to know
what's coming.

42:19.375 --> 42:21.375
( upbeat theme playing )
